# YieldWin — No-Loss Lottery Protocol

> **Win prizes. Never lose principal.**  
> Your USDC earns yield through Ondo RWA (USDY). When the pot reaches $2,000, Chainlink VRF randomly selects 5 winners. You can always withdraw 100% of your deposit.

---

## Architecture Overview

```
User deposits USDC
       │
       ▼
YieldWinVault (ERC-4626)
       │  mints 1 YWT ticket per 1 USDC
       │  converts USDC → USDY (Ondo Finance)
       ▼
USDY accrues yield daily via RWADynamicRateOracle
       │
       ▼
Chainlink Automation monitors: yield ≥ $2,000?
       │  yes → calls performUpkeep()
       ▼
Chainlink VRF v2.5 → fulfillRandomWords()
       │  LotteryLogic.selectWinners() → 5 unique winners
       ▼
Prize Distribution (80/10/10):
  • Grand winner:    60% of yield
  • 4 small winners: 5% each (20% total)
  • LP rewards:      10%
  • Treasury:        10%
```

## Prize Distribution

| Recipient       | Share  |
|-----------------|--------|
| Grand Winner    | 60%    |
| Small Winner ×4 | 5% each |
| LP Rewards      | 10%    |
| Treasury        | 10%    |

---

## Smart Contracts

| Contract           | Description |
|--------------------|-------------|
| `YieldWinVault.sol` | Main ERC-4626 vault, deposit/withdraw, draw trigger |
| `LotteryLogic.sol` | Library: 5-winner selection from single VRF seed |
| `mocks/MockContracts.sol` | MockUSDC, MockUSDY, MockUSDYOracle for testnet |
| `interfaces/IUSDYOracle.sol` | Ondo oracle interface |

### Security Features

- **Checks-Effects-Interactions** on all withdraw/redeem paths
- **48h lock-up**: deposits ineligible for draw and early-exit fee applies
- **Non-transferable tickets**: ERC-4626 shares are soulbound
- **Slippage protection**: 0.5% max slippage on USDC→USDY conversion
- **VRF uniqueness**: LotteryLogic guarantees 5 unique, non-zero winners
- **Pausable**: owner can pause in case of emergency
- **ReentrancyGuard**: on all external write functions

---

## Setup

### Prerequisites

- [Foundry](https://getfoundry.sh/) installed
- Node.js 18+
- Chainlink VRF v2.5 subscription on Arbitrum Sepolia

### 1. Install Foundry dependencies

```bash
forge install OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts@v5.0.0
forge install smartcontractkit/chainlink-brownie-contracts
forge install foundry-rs/forge-std
```

### 2. Environment variables

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

```env
PRIVATE_KEY=0x...
ARB_SEPOLIA_RPC=https://sepolia-rollup.arbitrum.io/rpc
ARBISCAN_API_KEY=...
VRF_SUBSCRIPTION_ID=...
LP_REWARD_ADDRESS=0x...
TREASURY_ADDRESS=0x...
USE_MOCKS=true
```

### 3. Deploy (testnet with mocks)

```bash
forge script script/DeployYieldWin.s.sol \
  --rpc-url $ARB_SEPOLIA_RPC \
  --broadcast \
  --verify \
  -vvvv
```

### 4. Post-deploy Chainlink setup

1. **VRF Subscription**: Go to [vrf.chain.link](https://vrf.chain.link), open your subscription, add the vault address as a consumer, and fund with LINK.

2. **Automation**: Go to [automation.chain.link](https://automation.chain.link), register a new upkeep:
   - Type: **Custom Logic**
   - Address: `<VAULT_ADDRESS>`
   - Fund with LINK

### 5. Test the draw (using mocks)

```bash
# Mint test USDC to a few wallets
cast send $MOCK_USDC "mint(address,uint256)" $USER1 10000000000 --rpc-url $ARB_SEPOLIA_RPC --private-key $PRIVATE_KEY

# Simulate 30 days of yield accrual on oracle
cast send $MOCK_ORACLE "simulateDays(uint256)" 30 --rpc-url $ARB_SEPOLIA_RPC --private-key $PRIVATE_KEY

# Check if draw is needed
cast call $VAULT "checkUpkeep(bytes)" "0x" --rpc-url $ARB_SEPOLIA_RPC
```

---

## Frontend

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
cp .env.local.example .env.local
# Set NEXT_PUBLIC_VAULT_ADDRESS, NEXT_PUBLIC_USDC_ADDRESS, NEXT_PUBLIC_WALLETCONNECT_PROJECT_ID
npm run dev
```

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

### Components

| Component | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `Dashboard.tsx` | TVL, jackpot meter, draw progress, user position |
| `Actions.tsx` | Approve → Deposit and Withdraw flows |
| `WinnerList.tsx` | Historical draws with winner addresses and prizes |

